  fhir:text [
     fhir:status [ fhir:v "extensions" ] ;
     fhir:div "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><p>This value set includes codes based on the following rules:</p><ul><li>Include these codes as defined in <a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html\"><code>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/condition-ver-status</code></a><table class=\"none\"><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b>Definition</b></td><td><b><a href=\"ConceptMap-CMVFencounterProblemVerificationStatus.html\">VF_encounterProblemVerificationStatus</a></b></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-provisional\">provisional</a></td><td style=\"color: #cccccc\">Provisional</td><td>This is a tentative diagnosis - still a candidate that is under consideration.</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-unconfirmed\">unconfirmed</a></td><td style=\"color: #cccccc\">Unconfirmed</td><td>There is not sufficient evidence to assert the presence of the subject's condition.</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-differential\">differential</a></td><td style=\"color: #cccccc\">Differential</td><td>One of a set of potential (and typically mutually exclusive) diagnoses asserted to further guide the diagnostic process and preliminary treatment.</td><td/></tr></table></li><li>Include these codes as defined in <code>http://va.gov/terminology/vistaDefinedTerms/9000010.07-.06</code><table class=\"none\"><tr><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b><a href=\"ConceptMap-CMVFencounterProblemVerificationStatus.html\">VF_encounterProblemVerificationStatus</a></b></td></tr><tr><td>C</td><td>CONSIDER</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-provisional\">provisional</a></td></tr><tr><td>D</td><td>DOUBTFUL</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-provisional\">provisional</a></td></tr><tr><td>F</td><td>FOLLOW UP</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-provisional\">provisional</a></td></tr><tr><td>M</td><td>MAYBE, POSSIBLE, PERHAPS</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-provisional\">provisional</a></td></tr><tr><td>P</td><td>PROBABLE</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-unconfirmed\">unconfirmed</a></td></tr><tr><td>O</td><td>RULE OUT</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-differential\">differential</a></td></tr><tr><td>S</td><td>SUSPECT, SUSPICIOUS</td><td><span title=\"EQUIVALENT\">~</span><a href=\"http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-condition-ver-status.html#condition-ver-status-provisional\">provisional</a></td></tr></table></li></ul></div>"
  ] ; # 
